<div id="review_3793077684" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3793077684" />
    <a title="Cindy Rollins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3480406-cindy-rollins"><img alt="Cindy Rollins" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1379169069p2/3480406.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3793077684?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cindy Rollins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cindy Rollins" href="/user/show/3480406-cindy-rollins">Cindy Rollins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/29354287-fathers-and-sons-centaur-classics-the-100-greatest-novels-of-all-time">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3480406-cindy-rollins?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3793077684" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer961035233040468643">About halfway through I would have e rated this a three-good but not great. But by the end I was astounded at the depths of the issues Turgenev covered between parents and adult children. So many of my own experiences captured throughout the later part of the book. The struggle of being a parent to adult children is covered in tenderness and grace. The struggle of youth and genius is also explored well. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


